MATERIALS AND METHODS: We used hospital claims for transurethral resection of 
the prostate from a 20% national sample of Medicare beneficiaries for the period 
1991 to 1997. Risk of mortality and reoperation were evaluated using life table 
methods and compared to those for the period 1984 to 1990. We also examined the 
