[Severe dysplasia in Barrett's esophagus].

[Article in Spanish]

Méndez JR(1), Sánchez G.

Author information:
(1)Hospital Gorgas.

Two patients with Barret's esophagus developed severe dysplasia diagnosed during 
endoscopic surveillance. Both patients underwent esophagectomy. The surgical 
specimen revealed adenocarcinoma in situ in the first patient and invasive 
adenocarcinoma to the submucosa in the second one. The life expectancy in these 
patients is at least 75% at 5 years, much better than the 5% five year survival 
of the patients diagnosed when they present with dysphagia. The natural history, 
pathogenesis, diagnosis, treatment and prevention are discussed.

